## Git Hook (Optional — Recommended)

To enforce this at the git level, add this to `.husky/pre-push` in the repo:

```bash
#!/bin/sh
CHANGED=$(git diff --name-only HEAD~1 HEAD 2>/dev/null | grep "PROJECT_STATUS.md")
STAGED=$(git diff --cached --name-only | grep "PROJECT_STATUS.md")

if [ -z "$CHANGED" ] && [ -z "$STAGED" ]; then
  echo "PUSH BLOCKED: PROJECT_STATUS.md has not been updated."
  echo "Update PROJECT_STATUS.md before pushing."
  echo "See .cursor/rules/project-status-enforcement.mdc for what to update."
  exit 1
fi

echo "PROJECT_STATUS.md updated — push allowed."
exit 0
```

This blocks the push if `PROJECT_STATUS.md` was not modified in the most recent commit. It can be bypassed with `--no-verify` when necessary.

**To install Husky in a repo that doesn't have it:**

```bash
npm install --save-dev husky
npx husky init
# Then replace .husky/pre-push with the script above
```
